    "introduction": "Bella Camero was born in Rio de Janeiro and grew up on the wings at the famed Tablado theater, watching her mom perform. There, she began her acting and improvisation lessons. She then went on to receive her Bachelor's Degree in Theater from UniverCidade. She made her TV debut in 2009's Geral.com for Rede Globo. Soon after, she starred as part of the main trio in the successful revival of the play Confissões de Adolescente, which went on to be adapted for the big screen. On TV, she was part of shows such as Malhação, A Grande Família and Onde Está Meu Coração. She also had a breakout role in HBO's Magnifica 70.Recently, she was part of the award-winning feature film Marighella, directed by Wagner Moura, as well as Netflix's Kissing Game, and another feature, Urubus, by Claudio Borelli, for which she received the Best Supporting Actress award at the British Independent Film Festival 2020. Bella is set to star in the upcoming Prime Video Original Series Lov3, which was shot in Uruguai, as well as Star+'s first Brazilian series, Insânia.",
